Angels to Sign Pitcher C.J. Wilson for Five Years, $75 Million, ESPN Says

-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 
2011-12-08T16:28:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/angels-to-sign-pitcher-c-j-wilson-for-five-years-75-million-espn-says.html
The Los Angeles Angels agreed to a
five-year contract with free-agent pitcher C.J. Wilson worth $75
million, ESPN reported, citing people it didn’t identify.  The Major League Baseball team also will sign  Albert Pujols 
to a 10-year deal worth between $250 million and $260 million,
Yahoo Sports reported earlier, citing a person it didn’t
identify.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  